DODGE: Toggle your combat mode to dodge incoming attacks

Syntax: dodge [on|off]

DESCRIPTION:
  Sets your combat mode to dodge instead of parry. Same toggle as
  autododge, just a shorter name.

  dodge          toggle dodge mode on or off
  dodge on       turn dodge mode on
  dodge off      turn dodge mode off, back to autoparry

  Parrying is the default mode: each incoming attack triggers a free
  parry roll (1d20 plus your parry bonus) with no cost. With dodge mode
  on, each incoming attack instead costs you 1 APM (Attack Per Melee) to
  attempt a dodge roll (1d20 plus your dodge bonus). Your dodge and
  parry bonuses come from your PP and level.

SEE ALSO: autododge, parry, autoparry, combat
